                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6294a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-21T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1913—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Your February 19, 5 p.m., and February 19, 10 p.m. The shooting of Gustavo
                    Madero caused a most unfavorable impression here. The President is gratified to
                    believe that there is no prospect of injury to the deposed President or Vice
                    President or their families.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
